ft class=m><span class=title> Re: My Take on Shadow Knights</span><hr size=1> You've got to take into account two different scenarios when you discuss SKs, grouped and solo.<br>
<br>
When grouped, your primary concern is AC and damage output.  Stats are nice, but they don't have much impact, even STR.  INT isn't terribly important either, because as mentioned above, mana regen is static and you won't want to be going OOM because of the increased downtime.  Most of your casting will be debuffs and the occasional lifetap to keep your health topped off.<br>
<br>
When solo, you need to find a good balance of AC, damage, and mana.  The level of the MOB you can take down is directly related to how much mana you have (how long you can keep it feared and darked) and how fast you can do damage.  If you are going for efficiency, then you'll need to find your own balance.  As a Troll, I have such a high regen, that I typically forego a fear or two and do some tanking.  With a high AC, I take minimal damage and regenerate the health while I'm medding.  The most efficient way for me to end a fight is down 30% HP and 40% mana, since they'll both hit full at about the same time.  At 51st, I've got 2100 HP, 1500+ MANA and a 926 self-buffed AC.  <br>
<br>
Don't underestimate natural regen at high levels.  If I'm not the puller, I'm getting back 12 HP per tick sitting, before any spells.  I generally also drop a Life Leech every other fight, and a few procs of Vampiric Embrace as well.  If I'm not the primary tank, my own lifetaps and regen mean I don't need heals, even if I take 500 or so damage per fight.  It also comes in handy to regen 6 per tick while feigned. <p>Krazaak Crushbone<BR>
51st Troll Reaver [Shadow Knight]<BR>
Isengard<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/unabum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>nabum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(4/11/01 1:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernclassdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=84.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My Take on Shadow Knights</span><hr size=1> AHHH well we all know bottom line shadowknights rock.<br>
